Governor Dapo Abiodun of Ogun State has reacted to the unrest in Abeokuta, state capital. DAILY POST had reported there was panic at Oluwo area of Abeokuta following the killing of a popular area boy known around the metropolis as Tommy, by alleged cultist. Tommy was reportedly killed Thursday night at Panseke, by some yet-to-be-identified persons. He was allegedly hacked to death with either an axe or a machete, leading to residents of the area fleeing. Reacting, Dapo in a tweet on his Twitter handle warned that he will deal decisively with anyone found wanting. He further stated that he has given the Commissioner of Police, Ogun State Command and other security agencies a marching order to go after those criminals He tweeted, “My attention has been drawn to the unrest going on in some parts of Abeokuta. Information available to me says these dastardly acts are being perpetrated by some criminals tagged cultists. “I have made it clear that we will deal decisively with anyone found wanting in this regard. “To this extent, I have given the Commissioner of Police, Ogun State Command and other security agencies a marching order to go after those criminals responsible for this crisis and restore total peace “Parents and guardians are also advised to warn their children an wards, as there will be no room for any form of plea for anybody culpable for these despicable and condemnable acts.”